<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Colors Property</title>

    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 30px;
            line-height: 1.8;
        }

        h1 {
            color: #2c3e50;
        }

        .color-name {
            color: crimson;
        }

        .hex {
            color: #3498db;
        }

        .rgb {
            color: rgb(46, 204, 113);
        }

        .rgba {
            color: rgba(231, 76, 60, 0.6);
        }

        .hsl {
            color: hsl(280, 80%, 45%);
        }

        .hsla {
            color: hsla(35, 100%, 50%, 0.7);
        }

        .yellow {
            background-color: yellow;
        }

        .green {
            background-color: lightgreen;
        }

        .blue {
            background-color: lightblue;
        }

        .text-bg {
            color: white;
            background-color: royalblue;
            padding: 10px;
        }

        .transparent {
            color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
        }

        .parent {
            color: darkorange;
        }

        .inherit {
            color: inherit;
        }

        .current {
            color: teal;
            border: 2px solid currentColor;
            padding: 10px;
            display: inline-block;
        }

        mark {
            background-color: gold;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>

    <h1>CSS Colors Property</h1>

    <h2>1. Color Name</h2>
    <p class="color-name">This text uses a color name.</p>

    <h2>2. HEX Color</h2>
    <p class="hex">This text uses a HEX color.</p>

    <h2>3. RGB Color</h2>
    <p class="rgb">This text uses RGB values.</p>

    <h2>4. RGBA Color</h2>
    <p class="rgba">This text uses RGBA with transparency.</p>

    <h2>5. HSL Color</h2>
    <p class="hsl">This text uses HSL values.</p>

    <h2>6. HSLA Color</h2>
    <p class="hsla">This text uses HSLA with transparency.</p>

    <h2>7. Background Highlight</h2>

    <p><span class="yellow">Yellow Highlight</span></p>
    <p><span class="green">Green Highlight</span></p>
    <p><span class="blue">Blue Highlight</span></p>

    <h2>8. Text + Background</h2>

    <p class="text-bg">
        White text with a blue background.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Transparent Text</h2>

    <p class="transparent">
        This text has low opacity.
    </p>

    <h2>10. inherit</h2>

    <div class="parent">
        Parent Text
        <p class="inherit">
            This paragraph inherits the parent's color.
        </p>
    </div>

    <h2>11. currentColor</h2>

    <div class="current">
        Border color is same as text color.
    </div>

    <h2>12. Highlight using &lt;mark&gt;</h2>

    <p>
        HTML also provides the
        <mark>mark tag</mark>
        to highlight important text.
    </p>

</body>
</html>